
List DVB tuner devices

Usage: tslsdvb [options]

Options:

  -a N
  --adapter N
      Specifies the Linux DVB adapter N (/dev/dvb/adapterN). This option can be
      used instead of device name.

  --debug[=level]
      Produce debug traces. The default level is 1. Higher levels produce more
      messages.

  -d name
  --device-name name
      Specify the DVB receiver device name, /dev/dvb/adapterA[:F[:M[:V]]] where
      A = adapter number, F = frontend number (default: 0), M = demux number
      (default: 0), V = dvr number (default: 0). By default, the first receiver
      device is used. Use the tslsdvb utility to list all DVB devices.

  --help
      Display this help text.

  -v
  --verbose
      Produce verbose output.

  --version
      Display the TSDuck version number.

